---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Terms of Service — YouTube to Notes AI"
  description="Read the Terms of Service for YouTube to Notes AI. Understand our terms of use, limitations of liability, and usage conditions."
>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container" style="max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto; padding-top: var(--spacing-2xl);">
      <span class="eyebrow">TERMS OF USE</span>
      <h1 style="font-size: 38px; margin-bottom: var(--spacing-lg);">Terms of Service</h1>
      
      <div class="card" style="margin-top: var(--spacing-xl); display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: var(--spacing-lg); font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.6; color: var(--color-body);">
        <p><em>Last Updated: June 10, 2026</em></p>
        
        <p>
          Welcome to YouTube to Notes AI! These terms and conditions outline the rules and regulations for the use of YouTube to Notes AI's Website, located at youtubetonotes.com.
        </p>

        <p>
          By accessing this website, we assume you accept these terms and service in full. Do not continue to use YouTube to Notes AI if you do not agree to take all of the terms and conditions stated on this page.
        </p>

        <h3 style="font-size: 20px; color: var(--color-ink); margin-top: var(--spacing-sm);">1. License and Fair Use</h3>
        <p>
          Unless otherwise stated, YouTube to Notes AI owns the intellectual property rights for all code, styling, and design elements on this site. You may access this for your personal use subject to restrictions set in these terms.
        </p>
        <p>
          You must not republish code or designs from YouTube to Notes AI, nor sell, rent, or sub-license materials from our platform.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>AI Generated Output:</strong> All notes, summaries, flashcards, and mind maps generated by the tool are the property of the respective user who initiated the request. We claim no ownership over your generated notes. You are free to print, distribute, and study them for personal or educational purposes.
        </p>

        <h3 style="font-size: 20px; color: var(--color-ink); margin-top: var(--spacing-sm);">2. Disclaimers</h3>
        <p>
          This tool retrieves YouTube transcripts publicly available on the internet. It does not hack, bypass premium paywalls, or download video files. 
        </p>
        <p>
          The AI notes are generated by Google's Gemini 2.0 Flash model. While the model is highly advanced, artificial intelligence can occasionally hallucinate, summarize points inaccurately, or misunderstand spoken words. All generated notes are provided "as-is", and we make no guarantees regarding their accuracy or suitability for official exams or professional reviews.
        </p>

        <h3 style="font-size: 20px; color: var(--color-ink); margin-top: var(--spacing-sm);">3. Limitation of Liability</h3>
        <p>
          In no event shall YouTube to Notes AI, nor any of its developers or affiliates, be liable for any direct, indirect, or consequential damages arising out of your use, or inability to use, this website, even if notified of the possibility of such damages.
        </p>

        <h3 style="font-size: 20px; color: var(--color-ink); margin-top: var(--spacing-sm);">4. Service Availability</h3>
        <p>
          We offer our tool 100% free of charge. We reserve the right to modify, suspend, or terminate the service (or any part thereof) at any time without notice, particularly if we hit Google Gemini API free-tier quotas or experience server overheads.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
